{
  "ELARA_CH1_ESTATE": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH1_ESTATE",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "Rain hammers against your hood as you stand in the shadow of what was your home.\n\nFive years. You count them in scars, in sleepless nights, in the cold calculation of revenge. The Vance Estate burns in your memory—not with fire that night, but with something worse: the silence after the blades found your parents' throats.\n\nThe official report called it a carriage accident. Lord Castellan signed the investigation papers himself, wearing your father's signet ring. He inherited the company, the house, the name. Everything.\n\nBut he didn't inherit you.\n\nYou're not the child who hid in the carriage that night, watching your father die. You're something else now. Something with teeth.\n\nThree paths lie before you: the careful path of information, the bleeding path of immediate action, or the winding path of building alliances. You have five years of patience stored like poison in your veins.\n\nWhat do you do?",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Gather information first", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH1_GATHER", "effects": {"intelligence": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Strike immediately", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH1_STRIKE", "effects": {"strength": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Find allies in the shadows", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH1_ALLIES", "effects": {"charisma": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH1_GATHER": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH1_GATHER",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You spend three months in the dark corners of Crownhaven, listening.\n\nThe Vance Trading Company's books are a labyrinth of falsified ledgers. Your father's 'accident' wasn't the first death Castellan arranged—and it won't be the last. You find records of merchants who 'retired' early, of partners who 'moved away,' of competitors whose ships 'disappeared.'\n\nBut you find something else. Your father's last deal before he died: a shipment from the eastern territories, contents classified. He sent it to the family vault before... before.\n\nThe vault is in Castellan's estate now. Guarded. Warded. But not impenetrable.\n\nYou also find chatter about the Ashfield Cult. They meet in old temples. They worship something called the Hollow. And Castellan attends their ceremonies.\n\nYour parents weren't killed for the company. They were killed for what they found.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Investigate the Cult connection", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH1_CULT", "effects": {"intelligence": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Study the vault's defenses", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH1_VAULT", "effects": {"stealth": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Contact your father's old contacts", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH1_CONTACTS", "effects": {"charisma": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH1_CULT": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH1_CULT",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "The Ashfield Cult meets in the burned Temple of Ash, three miles outside Thornwick.\n\nYou watch from the treeline as hooded figures gather in the moonlight. Their leader stands on the altar—a woman in black, her face hidden. She speaks of the Hollow, the void that existed before creation. She speaks of the crown, seven pieces scattered, seven fragments of power.\n\nOne of them mentions Castellan. 'The merchant prince pays for our protection. He provides cover for our operations.'\n\nYou understand now. Your father found something—a piece of the crown—and tried to destroy it. That's why they killed him. That's why they killed your mother.\n\nThe Cult must never reunite the crown. Your parents understood that. Now you do too.\n\nYou'll need allies for what's coming.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Find the Circle of Mages", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_NETWORK", "effects": {"intelligence": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Infiltrate as a initiate", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_INFILTRATE", "effects": {"stealth": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Track Castellan's movements", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_CONFRONT", "effects": {"dexterity": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH1_VAULT": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH1_VAULT",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You spend two weeks mapping the estate's defenses. Twelve guards, rotating shifts. Wards on the vault—a standard merchant's protection, nothing magical. Castellan cheats his taxes, not his security.\n\nBut you notice something: every third night, the guards change shifts at midnight. A five-minute window when the eastern wall is bare.\n\nYou also notice Castellan's habit: he visits the vault every week, alone. Never with guards. Whatever's inside, he wants to be the only one who sees it.\n\nThe piece of the crown calls to you. You've felt it since you were a child—that strange pull toward things that shouldn't exist. Your parents told you it was a gift. Now you know better.\n\nIt's a curse. And it's the only thing that can buy you the power you need.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Wait for the midnight window", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_NETWORK", "effects": {"stealth": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Confront Castellan directly", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_CONFRONT", "effects": {"strength": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Pose as a potential buyer", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_MEETING", "effects": {"charisma": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH1_CONTACTS": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH1_CONTACTS",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "Your father's old network is smaller than you remember—but more loyal.\n\nMarco, his old bookkeeper, weeps when he sees you. 'I knew you'd come back,' he whispers. 'Your father was the only good noble I ever met. The company was his heart.'\n\nHe's kept records—real records—of every transaction Castellan made. Every bribe, every forgery, every death. Your father was building a case against the Cult. He was gathering evidence.\n\n'He found something in the eastern shipment,' Marco says. 'A piece of an old crown. He wanted to destroy it. That's when they came for him.'\n\nHe gives you a key to the old family vault—and the name of a contact in the Circle of Mages. 'They can help you. If you let them.'\n\nYou have resources now. Information. A path forward.\n\nThe game begins.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Seek the Circle's help", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_NETWORK", "effects": {"intelligence": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Use the evidence against Castellan", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_CONFRONT", "effects": {"charisma": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Hit him where it hurts—his business", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_ATTACK", "effects": {"strength": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH1_STRIKE": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH1_STRIKE",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "Night. Castellan's study. He's working late, as usual—a贪婪 man never rests.\n\nYou slip through the servant's entrance. The guards don't notice you; they never do. Your father's study is ahead, warm light spilling under the door. You can hear him muttering about shipments, about profits, about the Cult's latest demands.\n\nThen you hear your name.\n\n'The Vance girl is still out there,' someone says. Castellan. 'Find her. Finish what we started.'\n\nYour hand finds your blade. Five years of patience燃烧 in a single heartbeat.\n\nBut you hesitate. Killing him won't answer your question: why did they die? What did they find?\n\nYou pull back from the door. Not yet. You need more information.\n\nFor now.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Leave—he's not worth it yet", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_NETWORK", "effects": {"humanity": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Attack anyway—now or never", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_ATTACK", "effects": {"combat": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Listen for more information", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH1_GATHER", "effects": {"intelligence": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH1_ALLIES": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH1_ALLIES",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You can't destroy a noble alone. You need an army of whispers.\n\nThe lower city is full of people with grudges—the dockworkers Castellan cheated, the merchants he ruined, the nobles he embarrassed. You gather them slowly, carefully. A reputation takes time, but it spreads.\n\nYour network grows: thieves who owe you favors, servants who hear things, guards who remember loyalty. You become the whisper in the shadows, the name people speak in dark corners.\n\nBy the third month, you have twelve reliable contacts. By the sixth, twenty-three. And somewhere in between, you realize: you're not just seeking revenge anymore. You're building something.\n\nA network becomes an organization. An organization becomes power. And power, in the right hands, becomes justice.\n\nCastellan doesn't know what's coming. But you do.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Move against Castellan", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_CONFRONT", "effects": {"charisma": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Infiltrate his inner circle", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_INFILTRATE", "effects": {"stealth": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Expand to the Cult", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH1_CULT", "effects": {"intelligence": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH2_NETWORK": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH2_NETWORK",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "The Circle of Mages hides in plain sight—a tower that appears different to each observer.\n\nYou climb the stairs, each step taking you further from the world you knew. The Archmage is ancient, her eyes holding centuries of knowledge.\n\n'We know why you're here,' she says. 'The crown piece. Castellan stole it from your parents.'\n\nShe explains: The crown is Aethon's crown—seven pieces, each containing a fragment of the first silence. United, they could unmake reality itself. The Cult wants that power. Your parents tried to destroy the piece they found. They died for it.\n\n'We can help you,' she offers. 'But the price is your service. Help us destroy the Cult, and we'll help you destroy Castellan.'\n\nYou have allies now. The question is: what are you willing to become?",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Accept their help", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_CIRCLE", "effects": {"intelligence": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Go your own way", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_CONFRONT", "effects": {"strength": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Infiltrate instead—get close", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_INFILTRATE", "effects": {"stealth": 2}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH2_CIRCLE": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH2_CIRCLE",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "The Circle trains you in ways you never imagined. Magic—or what passes for it in your blood. The void responds to your touch, dark and hungry.\n\n'The Vance family carries old blood,' the Archmage says. 'Your ancestor served Aethon. That's why the crown called to your parents. That's why it calls to you.'\n\nYou learn to pull shadows from the corners, to move without sound, to kill without痕迹. Your combat grows sharper. Your mind grows darker.\n\nIn three months, you're ready. The Circle has gathered intelligence: Castellan plans to sell the crown piece to the Cult's leader, Vespera. The transaction happens in one week.\n\nYou have one chance. Fail, and the Cult gets what they want. Succeed, and you get your answers.\n\nEverything builds to this.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Intercept the transaction", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_VAULT", "effects": {"combat": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Wait and gather more", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_MEETING", "effects": {"intelligence": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Strike at Castellan instead", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_ATTACK", "effects": {"strength": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH2_MEETING": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH2_MEETING",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You arrange a meeting with Castellan, posing as a merchant seeking investment.\n\nHis study is exactly as you remember. He wears your father's chair like a trophy. His eyes scan you, calculating.\n\n'You have your father's eyes,' he says. 'The same eyes that saw too much.'\n\nYour heart freezes. But your face remains calm.\n\n'I represent eastern interests,' you say. 'We have... mutual friends. The Cult speaks highly of your operations.'\n\nHis face goes pale. Then smooth. 'You've come a long way to die, girl.'\n\nGuards appear at the door. But you've planned for this.\n\nYour network moves in the shadows. Marco's evidence reaches the queen's council. Servants you've bribed spread word of his crimes. And somewhere in the city, your allies are burning his warehouses.\n\n'You made a mistake,' you tell him. 'You should have finished the job five years ago.'\n\nThe siege begins.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Give him a chance to confess", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_REVEAL", "effects": {"charisma": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Walk away—war is coming", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_VAULT", "effects": {"humanity": -1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Accept his surrender", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_SURRENDER", "effects": {"intelligence": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH2_ATTACK": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH2_ATTACK",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You don't wait. Five years of patience burns in a single heartbeat.\n\nYour blade finds the gap in his armor before his guards can react—straight through the heart. Lord Castellan gasps, more surprised than afraid.\n\n'You're...' he rasps. 'The Vance girl.'\n\n'The one you murdered,' you whisper. 'Say hello to my parents for me.'\n\nHe slumps. The guards finally react, but you're already through the window, vanishing into the night. The estate will be in chaos for hours.\n\nBut something is wrong. It was too easy. And in his study, you find something that changes everything: a letter from the Cult. Your parents didn't just find the crown piece—they tried to destroy it. The piece called to them, and they tried to unmake what was unmade.\n\nThat's why they died.\n\nYou have your revenge. But the question remains: what now?",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Search the vault—the crown calls", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_VAULT", "effects": {"stealth": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Flee the city—it's over", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_AFTERMATH", "effects": {"humanity": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Find the Cult—finish this", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_CULT", "effects": {"strength": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH2_INFILTRATE": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH2_INFILTRATE",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You join the Cult as an initiate. It takes three months of pretending to believe, of chanting words you don't understand, of watching ceremonies that make your stomach turn.\n\nBut you learn. You learn about their hierarchy, their plans, their leader. Vespera—the shadow lady—is more than a cult leader. She's something else. Something that burned and was reborn in the fires of the old temple.\n\nYou also learn about the crown. Six pieces gathered. One piece still missing— Castellan's piece.\n\nThey plan a ceremony: the Night of Convergence, when all seven pieces will unite. They call it the birth of a new world. You call it the end of everything.\n\nCastellan is supposed to deliver the piece tonight. And you're the only one who can stop it.\n\nThe question is: how far are you willing to go?",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Steal the piece during the ceremony", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_VAULT", "effects": {"stealth": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Reveal yourself—challenge Vespera", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_CONFRONT", "effects": {"charisma": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Signal the Circle—trap them all", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_CIRCLE", "effects": {"intelligence": 2}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH2_CONFRONT": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH2_CONFRONT",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You march into Castellan's study like you own the kingdom. Because soon, you will.\n\nHe looks up from his books, and recognition flickers in his eyes. 'You. The Vance girl.'\n\n'Me,' you say. 'Five years ago, you murdered my parents. You took everything. Now I'm here to take it back.'\n\nHis hand moves for the bell—but Marco's guards are already at the door. Your network. Your people.\n\n'Wait,' Castellan says. 'I can explain.'\n\nAnd he does. Your parents found the crown piece. They were going to destroy it. But the Cult made him do it—made him complicit. 'They would have killed me,' he says. 'They would have killed everyone I loved.'\n\nHe offers you a deal: the crown piece, yours to do with as you will. In exchange, you let him live.\n\nDo you take the deal?",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Take the deal—he's useless anyway", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_VAULT", "effects": {"intelligence": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Kill him—blood for blood", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_ATTACK", "effects": {"strength": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Turn him over to the Circle", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_CIRCLE", "effects": {"charisma": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH2_SURRENDER": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH2_SURRENDER",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You accept his surrender. A noble's death is too easy—it should be public, messy, remembered.\n\nThe evidence you've gathered goes to the queen's council. Charges of murder, fraud, Cult involvement. Castellan hangs in the public square three weeks later.\n\nBut in his study, you find what you truly sought: the vault key, and a letter explaining everything. Your parents found the crown piece. They tried to destroy it. The Cult killed them for their betrayal.\n\nThe piece is in the vault. And it's calling to you.\n\nYou have your justice. You have your answers. But you still have one choice left: what to do with the crown piece.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Take the piece—power is yours", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_TAKE", "effects": {"intelligence": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Destroy it—honor their wish", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_DESTROY", "effects": {"charisma": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Give it to the Circle", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_CIRCLE", "effects": {"intelligence": 2}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH2_REVEAL": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH2_REVEAL",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You step into the light. No more masks. No more pretending.\n\nCastellan's face goes white. 'You're—' But he doesn't finish.\n\n'Five years,' you say. 'I've watched. I've waited. I've built a network that could destroy you in a single night. But I'm not here to destroy you.'\n\nYou pull out your father's letter—the one he never got to send. 'I'm here to ask: why?'\n\nHis voice breaks. 'The Cult... they made me. My family, my children—they threatened them. Your parents found the crown piece and wanted to destroy it. I couldn't let them—the Cult would have killed everyone I love.'\n\n'But you killed them,' you say. 'My parents. In cold blood.'\n\n'I didn't,' he whispers. 'I tried to stop them. I failed.'\n\nThe truth hurts worse than the lie. He wasn't the mastermind—he was just a coward. And cowards are the most dangerous people in the world.\n\nNow you have your choice.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Forgive him—he's just a pawn", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_VAULT", "effects": {"humanity": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Kill him—no excuses", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_ATTACK", "effects": {"strength": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Turn him in—the law decides", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_SURRENDER", "effects": {"intelligence": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH3_VAULT": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH3_VAULT",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "The Vance family vault is exactly where you remember. The heavy iron door, the wards your father placed, the darkness that seems to breathe.\n\nInside, the crown piece waits on a pedestal. It's smaller than you imagined—a ring of black metal that seems to absorb light. When you touch it, the world goes silent.\n\nVisions flood your mind: Aethon the Undying, screaming as something beyond comprehension tears at his soul. The Void Beast. A god that eats gods. Aethon shattered his crown to keep it from falling into the Beast's hands. Seven pieces, scattered across time.\n\nYour parents understood. That's why they tried to destroy it. The piece in your hand could reunite the crown—and free something terrible.\n\nBut it could also give you power. Power to destroy the Cult. Power to protect everything your parents loved.\n\nPower always has a price.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Take it—use its power", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_TAKE", "effects": {"intelligence": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Destroy it—end the threat", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_DESTROY", "effects": {"charisma": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Give it to the Circle", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH3_CIRCLE", "effects": {"intelligence": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH3_TAKE": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH3_TAKE",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You take the crown piece. And everything changes.\n\nThe power floods through you—shadows, darkness, void. Your parents' memories become your memories. Their training becomes your training. Their enemies become your enemies.\n\nYou see the Cult's plans. The Night of Convergence. The sacrifices. The portal to the Void Beast. You see everything, spread before you like a map.\n\nYou feel unstoppable. You feel immortal. You feel... hungry.\n\nThe piece whispers to you, promising more. Six other pieces exist. Together, you could rule the world. Unmake your enemies. Create a new reality where everything is just, where nothing hurts.\n\nThe path to the Cult lies open. The path to Vespera lies open. The question is: what will you become?",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Find the other pieces—become power", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_CONFRONTATION", "effects": {"intelligence": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Destroy the Cult now", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_CONFRONTATION", "effects": {"combat": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Use it to destroy Castellan", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_REVENGE", "effects": {"strength": 2}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH3_DESTROY": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH3_DESTROY",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You destroy the crown piece. It takes everything—your parents' legacy, your birthright, your power. But it's done.\n\nThe piece shatters like glass, releasing something older than light. Your parents' spirits, perhaps. Or just the emptiness they tried to protect.\n\nWithout the piece, the Cult's plan fails. The Night of Convergence becomes just another failed ritual. Vespera screams in the distance—you feel it.\n\nCastellan falls to the Circle's justice. The evidence you've gathered cleans up the rest of his network. The kingdom breathes easier.\n\nBut you're empty. The power you could have had, the answers you might have found—all gone.\n\nYou have your vengeance. But you also have a choice: what now? Without the piece, you have no destiny. You have only the life you build.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Join the Circle—find new purpose", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_EXPOSE", "effects": {"intelligence": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Walk away—it's over", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_AFTERMATH", "effects": {"humanity": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Continue hunting the Cult", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_EXPOSE", "effects": {"combat": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH3_CIRCLE": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH3_CIRCLE",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You give the piece to the Circle. They promise to destroy it properly, to seal it away where no one can ever find it.\n\nThe Archmage looks at you with something like respect. 'Your parents would be proud,' she says. 'They tried to do this. You succeeded.'\n\nBut you feel the loss. The piece called to you—your family's legacy, your birthright. Without it, you're just another survivor.\n\nThe Circle offers you a place. Not as a mage—they see your potential, but it's too late—but as a hunter. The Cult remains, scattered but not destroyed. Vespera remains, wounded but not beaten.\n\nThey want you to finish the job. And you want the same thing.\n\nThe war isn't over. It's just changing form.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Accept—the hunt continues", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_EXPOSE", "effects": {"combat": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Refuse—you've done enough", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_AFTERMATH", "effects": {"humanity": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Hunt Vespera yourself", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_REVENGE", "effects": {"strength": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH3_CULT": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH3_CULT",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You find the Cult's temple—a burned-out ruin where they practice their rituals.\n\nThey're preparing for something: the Night of Convergence, when all seven pieces of the crown will unite. They have six already. Without Castellan's piece, they're missing one—but they have plans to get it.\n\nThe leader, Vespera, is something else. She was a princess, once—a saint of the old Light. The fire changed her. The void remade her. She's beautiful and terrible, and she's waiting for you.\n\n'I knew you'd come,' she says. 'The Vance blood calls to the crown. And you're the last of it.'\n\nShe offers you a choice: join her, and help complete the Convergence. Or die here, like your parents.\n\nThe choice is easy.",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Fight her—end this now", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_CONFRONTATION", "effects": {"combat": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Join her—become the power", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_CONSUMED", "effects": {"strength": -1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Bargain—give her the piece", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_NEGOTIATE", "effects": {"charisma": 1}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH4_CONFRONTATION": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH4_CONFRONTATION",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "The final confrontation. The Cult's temple, burning with void light. Vespera stands at the center of the ritual, six crown pieces circling her like dying stars.\n\n'You're too late,' she says. 'The Convergence is almost complete. Soon, the Hollow will rise. The old god will wake. And the world will be remade.'\n\nBut she needs the seventh piece—yours. Without it, the ritual fails. Without it, she can't free the Void Beast.\n\nThe pieces call to each other. The empty space in the circle waits. Your piece responds, hungry.\n\nThis is the moment. The choice. The end.\n\nWhat do you do?",
    "choices": [
      {"letter": "A", "text": "Use the piece to seal the Beast—be the hero", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_EXPOSE", "effects": {"charisma": 2}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "B", "text": "Give in—become the power", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_CONSUMED", "effects": {"intelligence": 1}, "requires": null},
      {"letter": "C", "text": "Kill Vespera—personal revenge", "leads_to": "ELARA_CH4_REVENGE", "effects": {"combat": 2}, "requires": null}
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH4_EXPOSE": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH4_EXPOSE",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You use the crown piece to complete the seal—the ancient binding that held the Void Beast once. It won't hold forever, but it will hold for now.\n\nThe sixth piece responds to your will. The ritual shatters. Vespera screams as the power rips through her—but it's not destruction. It's banishment.\n\nThe Cult scatters. The pieces scatter. And you stand in the ruins, holding the power to either save the world or destroy it.\n\nYou choose to seal it away. The Circle helps you—all seven pieces, hidden in places only you know. The Void Beast sleeps again.\n\nThe kingdom calls you a hero. But you don't need their praise. You have your justice.\n\nYour parents rest, finally. And you?\n\nYou have the rest of your life to decide what comes next.",
    "type": "ending",
    "ending": "ELARA_JUDGE"
  },
  "ELARA_CH4_CONSUMED": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH4_CONSUMED",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You hand over the crown piece. And you feel yourself change.\n\nThe power floods through you—seven pieces as one. The seal breaks. The Void Beast stirs.\n\nAnd you're the one who controls it now. Not Vespera. Not the Cult. You.\n\nThe world reshapes itself around you. The kingdoms fall. The old temples rise again. You rule from a throne of shadow, and the world calls you by a new name: the Hollow Queen.\n\nIt's not evil, exactly. It's just different. The pain is gone. The loss is gone. Everything is silence, and silence is peace.\n\nYour parents would be horrified. But your parents are gone. And you have eternity to make them understand.\n\nIn the end, you become what you hunted. You become the monster. And somehow, that's alright.",
    "type": "ending",
    "ending": "ELARA_CONSUMED"
  },
  "ELARA_CH4_REVENGE": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH4_REVENGE",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "Vespera falls. The Cult falls. Everything falls.\n\nThe crown pieces scatter, useless without the ritual. The Void Beast sleeps, forever untouched. And you stand in the center of the ruins, your blade wet with the blood of your enemy.\n\nIt doesn't feel like victory. It doesn't feel like anything.\n\nYou remember your parents, crying in the carriage that night. You remember the silence after the blades found their throats. You remember five years of waiting, of planning, of becoming something with teeth.\n\nAnd now it's over. The vengeance you sought for half your life is complete. And you're left with nothing but the emptiness.\n\nThe road calls to you. Other Cults exist. Other monsters wait. Other people need saving.\n\nBut not tonight. Tonight, you just walk.\n\nThe Avenger walks forever. And somewhere in the darkness, she keeps walking.",
    "type": "ending",
    "ending": "ELARA_AVENGER"
  },
  "ELARA_CH4_NEGOTIATE": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH4_NEGOTIATE",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You bargain with Vespera. And somehow, you win.\n\nThe piece is hers—but so is your service. You become her instrument, her hunter, her edge. The Cult grows stronger with you at its side.\n\nBut you play the long game. Years pass. Decades. You gather information, allies, power. You wait for the moment to strike.\n\nAnd when it comes, it comes hard. The Cult falls. Vespera falls. And you stand in the ashes, the crown piece in your hand, the power you were promised finally yours.\n\nYou don't use it to rule. You don't use it to destroy. You use it to ensure no one else ever suffers as you suffered.\n\nThe Avenger becomes the Protector. The monster becomes the guardian. It's not what you expected.\n\nBut it's what you needed.",
    "type": "ending",
    "ending": "ELARA_JUDGE"
  },
  "ELARA_CH4_AFTERMATH": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH4_AFTERMATH",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "The war is over. Castellan is dead—or ruined. The Cult is scattered—or destroyed. And you?\n\nYou walk away. The road stretches ahead, endless and empty. You have no cause, no purpose, no destiny. Just the skills you built, the network you gathered, the power you carry.\n\nOther Cults exist. Other monsters wait. Other people need saving.\n\nBut not tonight. Tonight, you just walk.\n\nThe Avenger walks forever. In the darkness, she keeps searching—for answers, for peace, for something that might feel like home.\n\nShe never finds it. But she never stops looking.\n\nThat's what makes her the Avenger.",
    "type": "ending",
    "ending": "ELARA_AVENGER"
  }
}
